added.title: Tower Power
added.description: Cyborg plugs into the control panel of the Titans' tower and drives the others crazy.

added.title: Parasite
added.description: Starfire's new pet is a horribly dangerous parasite, but Robin is the only one who is suspicious of the beast.

added.title: Starliar
added.description: Beast Boy teaches Starfire how to lie and it backfires as her lies get more and more outrageous.

added.title: Staff Meeting
added.description: When the gang breaks Robin's beloved staff, Robin is forced to find a replacement.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Party
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are invited to a high school party, and have to bring a date!

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: The Robot
added.description: Gumball discovers that Bobert is planning to take over his identity and replace him!

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: Kelsey Quest
added.description: Kelsey accepts a quest from the Elders of the Creek, but is she ready for her terrifying opponent?

added.title: JPony
added.description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Steven the Sword Fighter
added.description: Pearl tries to teach Steven the art of sword-fighting using a holographic version of himself.

added.title: Lion 2: The Movie
added.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

added.title: Beach Party
added.description: After a battle damages Fish Stew Pizza, Steven throws a cookout at the Temple to mend the relationship between Pizza family and the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Rose's Room
added.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

added.title: Coach Steven
added.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

added.title: Freak City
added.description: A magical man turns Finn into a foot. They meet others who have been similarly wronged and must work together.

added.title: Ocean of Fear
added.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet, overcoming his fear of water.

added.title: When Wedding Bells Thaw
added.description: Finn must help plan the Ice King's bachelor party.

added.title: The Duke
added.description: Finn goes to great lengths to catch the evil Duke of Nuts, only to discover he's not such a bad guy after all.

added.title: Skips vs. Technology
added.description: Skips wants to help Mordecai and Rigby with their computer problems.

added.title: Butt Dial
added.description: Mordecai pocket dials an embarrassing message on Margaret's phone.

added.title: Eggscellent
added.description: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby.

added.title: Gut Model
added.description: Muscle Man becomes a model.

added.title: Video Game Wizard
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby enter a video game tournament to win a video game controller.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Man Up 2: Still Man-ing
added.description: When someone steals all the water in Townsville, it's up to the girls to race through the Townsville Wastelands to get it back.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Lizard Day Afternoon
added.description: Clarence and Sumo chase a lizard to unexpected rewards as Jeff jockeys for playing time on Belson's spectacular new gaming system.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Wicked Shades
added.description: When Pizza Steve borrows Uncle Grandpa's sunglasses, he sees things in a whole new light.

added.title: Except for Cooper
added.description: A young boy must learn to eat his spinach in order to save Uncle Grandpa and the others from a rowdy gang of evil vegetables.

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: The Lepre-Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

added.title: Mr. McStuffles/Twinkle, Baby Looney Star (song)/Picture This!
added.description: Mr. McStuffles: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it./Picture This: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/A Clean Sweep
added.description: Hair Cut-Ups: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut./A Clean Sweep: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Pig Who Cried Woof
added.description: Daffy Did It!: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying./The Pig Who Cried Wolf: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

added.title: New Cat in Town/Baby Bunny (song)/The Magic of Spring
added.description: New Cat in Town: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving./The Magic of Spring: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

added.title: For Whom the Toll Calls/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Cereal Boxing
added.description: For Whom the Toll Calls: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill./Cereal Boxing: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

added.title: Taz in Toyland/Born to Sing (song)/A Secret Tweet
added.description: Taz in Toyland: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something./A Secret Tweet: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

added.title: Comfort Level/Twinkle Baby Looney Star (song)/Like a Duck to Water
added.description: Comfort Level: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey./Like a Duck to Water: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

added.title: School Daze/Mary Had a Baby Duck (song)/Things That Go Bugs in the Night
added.description: School Daze: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing./Things That Go Bugs in the Night: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

added.title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip/The Looney Riddle (song)/Card Bored Box
added.description: Creature from the Chocolate Chip: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame./Card Bored Box: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

added.title: Time and Time Again/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/May the Best Taz Win
added.description: Time and Time Again: The babies learn the importance of telling time./May the Best Taz Win: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

added.title: Mine!/Over the Burrow (song)/Sylvester the Pester
added.description: Mine!: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money./Sylvester the Pester: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

added.title: Cat-Taz-Trophy/If You're Looney (song)/Duck! Monster! Duck!
added.description: Cat-Taz-Trophy: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby./Duck! Monster! Duck!: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

added.title: The Brave Little Tweety/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Puddle Olympics
added.description: The Brave Little Tweety: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero./The Puddle Olympics: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Mother's Day Madness
added.description: A Lot Like Lola: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her./Mother's Day Madness: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/To Tell the Tooth
added.description: Takers Keepers: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want./To Tell the Tooth: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

added.title: Spin Out/Taz's Fridge (song)/Snow Day
added.description: Spinout: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy./Snow Day: The babies experience their first snowfall.

added.title: Shadow of a Doubt/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Christmas in July
added.description: Shadow of a Doubt: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is./Christmas in July: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

added.title: Bruce Bunny/Baby Bunny (song)/Leader of the Pack
added.description: Bruce Bunny: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce./Leader of the Pack: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

added.title: Flower Power/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Lightning Bugs Sylvester
added.description: Flower Power: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden./Lightning Bugs Sylvester: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

added.title: Flush Hour/Paws and Feathers (song)/I Strain
added.description: Flush Hour: The babies learn the purpose of toilets./I Strain: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Some Assembly Required
added.description: The Sandman Is Coming: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes./Some Assembly Required: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up/My Bunny Lies Over the Ocean (song)/Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: All Washed Up: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath./Did Not! Did Too!: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball/Down by the Cage (song)/Taz You Like It
added.description: Tea & Basketball: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys./Taz You Like It: Taz discovers pratfalls get him laughs and attention.

added.title: Band Together/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/War of the Weirds
added.description: Band Together: The babies learn about music and improvise their own orchestra./War of the Weirds: Marvin the Martian comes to visit, and the babies learn to accept differences.

added.title: The Harder They Fall/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/Business as Unusual
added.description: The Harder They Fall: Bugs is embarrassed to admit he doesn't know how to skate./Business as Unusual: Bugs and Daffy open competing lemonade stands.

added.title: Who Said That?/Paws and Feathers (song)/Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Who Said That?: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it./Let Them Make Cake: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Mind Your Manners/Down by the Cage (song)/Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: Mind Your Manners: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny./Petunia the Piggy Bank: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Pouting Match
added.description: A Pastime for Petunia: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests./Pouting Match: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Wise Quacker/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
added.description: Wise Quacker: Bugs gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but he takes the jokes too far./Yours, Mine...and Mine Mine Mine!: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

added.title: Loose Change/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/Act Your Age
added.description: Loose Change: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change./Act Your Age: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

added.title: Who's Your Granny?/If You're Looney (song)/The Tattletale
added.description: Who's Your Granny?: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities./The Tattletale: Lola begins tattling on the other babies until her friends no longer want to play with her.

added.title: The Yolk's on You/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Baby-Gate
added.description: The Yolk's on You: Daffy and Melissa team up to play jokes on the other babies./Baby Gate: Melissa spreads rumors about the babies, and Bugs goes undercover to find the truth.

added.title: Never Say Try/Taz's Fridge (song)/Pair O' Dice Lost
added.description: Never Say Try: Sylvester is a bad dancer and finger painter so he believes he'll never be good at anything./Pair O' Dice Lost: Daffy feels defeated whenever things aren't going his way.

added.title: Melissa the Hero/My Bunny Lies over the Ocean (song)/The Trouble with Larry
added.description: Melissa the Hero: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement./The Trouble with Larry: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

added.title: The Littlest Tweety/Over the Burrow (song)/In Bugs We Trust
added.description: The Littlest Tweety: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size./In Bugs We Trust: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

added.title: Cool for Cats/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Time Out!
added.description: Cool for Cats: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool./Time Out!: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

added.title: Present Tense/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/The Neat and the Sloppy
added.description: Present Tense: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own./The Neat and the Sloppy: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

added.title: Tell-A-Photo/Born to Sing (song)/Move It!
added.description: Tell-A-Photo: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together./Move It!: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

removed.title: Bring Out Your Beast
removed.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

removed.title: My Clique
removed.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

removed.title: Matched
removed.description: When a computer dating program matches Beast Boy to Raven, he tries wooing her to disastrous effect.

removed.title: Terra-ized
removed.description: Beast Boy falls for Terra despite clear signs that she is more interested in destroying the Titans.

removed.title: The Future is Cardboard
removed.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

removed.title: Arcade Mania
removed.description: Steven takes the Crystal Gems to Funland Arcade where Garnet learns the allure of video games.

removed.title: Man of the House
removed.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

removed.title: Dog Decider
removed.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

removed.title: Dream Boat

removed.title: The Brood
removed.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

removed.title: Rise and Shine
removed.description: A glimpse at the wild, secret adventures Clarence undertakes each day before the rest of us, and the sun, get up.

removed.title: Stuck in an Elevator
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to a reunion concert.

removed.title: Treasure Map
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

removed.title: Jorts
removed.description: When Mr. Gus gets stuck in an embarrassingly super tight pair of jorts, he has to somehow get out of them in order to save his friends.

removed.title: The Mustache
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

removed.title: Arachno Romance
removed.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

removed.title: Space Escape
removed.description: The guys have to escape from someone bad.

removed.title: The Space Race
removed.description: The guys race in space.

removed.title: Onion Trade
removed.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

removed.title: Brain Game
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

removed.title: Brother Up
removed.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

removed.title: Can You Ear Me Now?
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby offend some people.

removed.title: Giant Woman
removed.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

removed.title: The Ape
removed.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

removed.title: Finn Meets His Hero
removed.description: Finn meets his adventuring role model, only to learn he's become a wuss in his old age.

removed.title: Zoo
removed.description: Clarence and Belson make a true odd couple when they're paired up during a field trip to the zoo and find themselves locked inside after hours.

removed.title: So Many Birthdays
removed.description: So Many Birthdays: Steven learns that the Crystal Gems are thousands of years old and decides to make up for all the thousands of birthdays they've missed.

removed.title: Charlie
removed.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

removed.title: Puffdora's Box
removed.description: When Blossom gets overzealous with the spring cleaning, she accidentally unleashes a group of evil spirits.

removed.title: Colors of Raven
removed.description: A magical prism causes Raven to fragment into five distinct personalities which wreak havoc around town until the other Titans can figure out how to rejoin her.

removed.title: Occupy Bears
removed.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

removed.title: Burger vs. Burrito
removed.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy face off about which is better, burgers or burritos.

removed.title: Operation: Hear No Evil
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to avoid spoilers of their favorite TV show.

removed.title: Lost in the Sewer
removed.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

removed.title: The Club
removed.description: When Gumball rejects "The Rejects Club", the rejects wreak their revenge.

removed.title: Tiara Trouble
removed.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

removed.title: The Date
removed.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

removed.title: What Have You Done?
removed.description: Finn and Jake befriend the Ice King in an attempt to save the ice cream people.

removed.title: Lars and the Cool Kids
removed.description: Steven and Lars get to hang out with the cool kids in town, but their teenage shenanigans get them into magical trouble.

removed.title: Afraid of the Dark
removed.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

removed.title: Puddle Eyes
removed.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

removed.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
removed.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

removed.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
removed.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

removed.title: Henchman
removed.description: While trying to rescue a helpless stranger, Finn becomes Marceline's slave.

removed.title: Shush Ninjas
removed.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

removed.title: The Wand
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin make their dad believe in magic again.

removed.title: Artful Dodgers
removed.description: The Titans revert to creative game-playing in order to have a chance at beating the undefeated supervillain dodgeball team.

removed.title: Rainy Day Daydream
removed.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.
